\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Often choice controls are driven by data that changes. In this case, it is useful to use a data source to set the item and display lists for the control.\par
\par
In this example, the same data source is used for both choice controls. A Category code is used to select which set of data is displayed within the choice list. Using one generic code table is a convenient way to deal with the many small lists that are needed in applications.\par
\par
Also in this example, two sets of data are combined in the Description field. This enables two different fields to show on one list.\par
\par
The Add car button will add an entry to the cars list and refresh the control using the ControlItemsRefresh function.\par
}
